# =============================================================================
# @app/web — Environment Variable Template (web client subset)
# =============================================================================
# Copy this file to `packages/web/.env` when running the web package on its own:
#
#     cp packages/web/.env.example packages/web/.env
#
# Vite also auto-loads `.env.local` (which is git-ignored) if you prefer to keep
# machine-specific overrides out of `.env`.
#
# In normal operation you do NOT need this copy: `make local` / `make up` load
# the ROOT `.env` (a superset that also carries the server-only vars and the
# docker-compose POSTGRES_* values), and the Vite dev server — launched from the
# repo root via `pnpm --filter @app/web dev` — reads the VITE_* vars from it.
# This per-package template documents the exact subset the web client needs;
# keep its variable names and values in sync with the root `.env.example`.
#
# SECURITY BOUNDARY: Vite exposes ONLY variables prefixed with `VITE_` to the
# browser (via `import.meta.env`). Everything else stays server-side. Anything
# placed in this file is bundled into client-side JavaScript and is therefore
# public — NEVER add a secret here. Server-only variables (NODE_ENV,
# DATABASE_URL, REDIS_URL, JWT_SECRET, JWT_EXPIRES_IN, FILE_UPLOAD_PATH,
# MAX_FILE_SIZE_MB, API_PORT) live in the root `.env.example` and
# `packages/api/.env.example`.
#
# Format rules: one KEY=VALUE per line; no quotes around values; no shell-style
# ${INTERPOLATION} (dotenv parsers differ); placeholders only — never commit a
# real secret. See /docs/decision-log.md for the rationale behind each choice.
# =============================================================================

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# API endpoints
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Base URL the web client uses for all HTTP REST calls. Consumed by the fetch
# wrapper in src/lib/api-client.ts, which prepends it to every /api/* request.
VITE_API_URL=http://localhost:3000
# Socket.io endpoint URL, consumed by the singleton in src/lib/socket.ts. The
# Socket.io server is mounted on the same HTTP server as Express, so this shares
# the API origin; the socket.io-client upgrades to the WebSocket transport
# internally. Normally identical to VITE_API_URL.
VITE_WS_URL=http://localhost:3000

# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# Web app origin
# -----------------------------------------------------------------------------
# The web client's OWN dev-server origin. The Vite dev server listens on 5173 by
# default (the API uses 3000). Used by playwright.config.ts (baseURL) for E2E
# runs and by the API CORS allow-list so the browser can reach the API from
# this origin.
VITE_APP_URL=http://localhost:5173
